MissionTemplate.name: Low Altitude CAP
MissionTemplate.description: Conduct low altitude air patrol over Glubokovskij, focusing on protecting ground forces from air threats.

Pilot.name: Wolfe Hummel
Pilot.Background: The son of a railway station manager in Königsberg, Wolfe Hummel grew up watching freight trains vanish toward the east. he volunteered for the Luftwaffe shortly after finishing school, seeking adventure and to serve the Reich from above. he had no formal aviation experience but scored highly in spatial recognition and mathematics. During training, he developed a reputation for precise formation flying. A friend from his training unit was killed in a crash, which left a lasting impression on Wolfe Hummel.
